# Line endings. This repo is authored on Windows and RUNS ON LINUX (droplet + containers), so
# the working tree is normalised to LF rather than left to core.autocrlf.
#
# Without this, a clone on a machine with `core.autocrlf=true` gets CRLF on disk, Docker
# bind-mounts scripts/init-test-db.sh into the postgres container, and Linux fails with
# `#!/bin/sh^M: bad interpreter`. The file is fine in the repo — it breaks on checkout, which
# is the sort of bug that only ever appears on someone else's fresh clone.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows-only launchers: these are read by cmd.exe, so leave them CRLF.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Never touch these — normalisation would corrupt them.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.mp3 binary
*.wav binary
*.onnx binary
*.tflite binary
*.db binary
